  "title": "Associate Engineer, R& D Process/ Equipment Development",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description;</strong></p><ul><li>Expertise in root cause analysis and problem solving</li><li>Provide process / machine improvement and implementation of process / machine in development / mass production</li><li>Support customer prototype, engineering, qualification builds</li><li>Execute process characterization / DOE activities and generate report for submission & presentation</li><li>Lead / Support failure analysis and root cause investigation, and generate FACA report & presentation</li><li>Work with third party and identify solutions to enhance process / machines capabilities</li><li>Coordinate all customers prototype, engineering, qualification builds with cross function teams to maximize our resources</li><li>Monitor & track the progress of key deliverables to achieve defined Key Milestone and Success Criteria for process / machine including regular communication with process / development engineers, Program Manager, suppliers and customers</li><li>Set & monitor the KPI base on process / development projects</li></ul><p><strong>Requirement:</strong></p><ul><li>Min Diploma in Material Science, Applied Physics, Mechanical Engineering or related engineering discipline</li><li>Min 3-5 years working experience in the related field</li></ul>",
